 The  5000 metres  or  5000-meter run  (approximately 3.1 mi or 16,404 ft) is a common  long-distance running  event in  track and field . It is one of the track events in the  Olympic Games  and the  World Championships in Athletics , run over 12.5 laps of a standard track. The same distance in  road running  is called a  5K run . The 5000 m has been present on the Olympic programme since 1912 for men and since 1996 for women. Prior to 1996, women had competed in an Olympic  3000